<br>
Now, I don't feel like I've hurt myself and have done well for 47 levels. But I just wish I had those few extra HP <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src=http://www.legendarydefenders.com/pics/zzy.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/urenaebi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Renaebi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/3/02 9:17:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1745.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Recommended Beastlord Starting Stats?</span><hr size=1> HP is nice, and so is not losing stats when you get fatiqued.  I made sure I got my Vahshir to 100 STA then dumped the rest into WIS.  On an Iksar, you start with great WIS for a hybrid, so I would dump it all into STA. <p><select name="eternus"><option value="1">Yiktiki Tumbo - 24 Vahshir Beastlord</option><option value="2" SELECTED>Renaebi Shurai - 55 Human Master (semi-retired)</option><option value="3">Shaerl - 51 Barbarian Rake (semi-retired)</option><option value="4">Starlighte Starbrighte - 29 Wood Elf Druid (retired)</option>	<option value="6">----------------------------------------------------------</option><option value="7">Free Agent</option><option value="8">Innoruuk Server</option></select></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ubeastofwar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beast of War</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/3/02 9:33:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1745.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Recommended Beastlord Starting Stats?</span><hr size=1> Yeah, put them into STA if you're going iksar. As Renaebi mentioned, Iksars start out with the great WIS (highest wisdom amongst the races that can be Beastlords), so its no big loss when you pump that Stamina ability up.<br>
<br>
I'd say you'll be better off as an ogre in the stat departmnt, but I am kinda biased <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><b>Ukog</b><br>
<b><a href= "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227089"><i>The Beast of War</i></a></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uhekal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hekal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>mewling</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#871F78>(7/4/02 12:58:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1745.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Recommended Beastlord Starting Stats?</span><hr size=1> What about if you are Vah Shir?<br>
<br>
For now Im thinkin 15 Sta and 5 Wis? <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uhekal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hekal</A> at: 7/4/02 12:59:19 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ulaocus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laocus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast in Training</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#871F78>(7/4/02 1:19:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1745.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Recommended Beastlord Starting Stats?</span><hr size=1> A lot of this depends on how much of a &quot;powergamer&quot; you are and your access to good items.  <br>
<br>
Stamina gives you more hitpoints, but the difference is not that great until high levels.  True, it is the hardest stat to raise through items, but unless you're going to be twinked or Powerleveled, then I would suggest putting most of your points into wisdom, as it will make the journey to higher levels easier, particularly if you are new to the game or to the class.<br>
<br>
If, however, you have a high level character and will be twinking this new guy, definitely STA all the way.<br>
<br>
My 2cp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ujatarus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jatarus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast Prince</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#871F78>(7/4/02 8:01:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1745.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>   Recommended beastlord starting stats</span><hr size=1>  It pretty much depends on the player and if your are in a guild or even a higher end guild for that matter.<br>
